{"key":"processedPost-7821736","value":{"id":7821736,"first":7815537,"last":7822264,"when":1199247383,"utime":"01/02/08 06:16 AM","content":"In addition, you don't sterilize agar in the petri dishes. You sterilize agar in a filtered jar or bottle, and then pour into the dishes when it cools to just above where it solidifies. You don't remove plastic dishes from the sterile sleeve until they're in your glovebox and you're ready to pour.  A sleeve of 20 sterile plastic dishes will cost from $4 to $6, depending on where you shop.  If they charged six bucks for one, you got ripped.<br /><br />There's lots of so-called 'teks' written by complete noobs who dream something up and instead of posting \"I wonder if this idea would work?\", they post it as an actual tek, which then becomes searchable as 'tek' and others get bit in the ass.<br />RR","title":"Re: melting dishes"}}